<paragraph blockId="2.[151,702,1614,1674]" box="[151,235,1649,1674]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1649,1674]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,295,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,257,1890]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Anufrievia arcuata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. style; d. connective; e. aedeagus, ventral view; f. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444102/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1721,1962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Body orange yellowish. Transition area from vertex to face orange at central part. Eyes and basal triangles of mesonotum blackish. Pronotum with whitish dumbbell-shaped streak near middle anterior margin. Fore wing beige.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1721,1962]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,1829,1854]" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Pygofer with about 4 macrosetae at cephalo-ventral angle of lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1249,1829,1854]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,295,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,257,1890]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Anufrievia arcuata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. style; d. connective; e. aedeagus, ventral view; f. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444102/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
), apex of dorsal appendage not bifurcated, base broad, tapering to apex (
<figureCitation box="[803,890,1865,1890]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,295,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,257,1890]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Anufrievia arcuata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. style; d. connective; e. aedeagus, ventral view; f. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444102/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
). Style with apical tooth shorter than subapical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[223,305,1901,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,295,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,257,1890]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Anufrievia arcuata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. style; d. connective; e. aedeagus, ventral view; f. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444102/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft broad in lateral view, almost straight, apical processes symmetric, hooked in ventral view; preatrial process developed, slightly sinuated, apex reaching gonopore; gonopore subapical (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1366,1937,1962]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,295,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,257,1890]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Anufrievia arcuata Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage; c. style; d. connective; e. aedeagus, ventral view; f. aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444102/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="205">Figs 2e, f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
